<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0da2435e-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21052"><num value="21052">§ 21052.</num><heading> Report</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0da2435f-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21052/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each entity which receives a grant under this subpart shall submit to the Commission a report describing the activities carried out with the funds provided under the grant.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0da24360-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21052/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Deadline</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">An entity shall submit a report required under subsection (a) not later than 60 days after the end of the fiscal year for which the entity received the grant which is the subject of the report.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id0da24361-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/252/tII/s282">Pub. L. 107–252, title II, § 282</ref>, <date date="2002-10-29">Oct. 29, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1702">116 Stat. 1702</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
